HTTP STATUS CODES
401 Unauthorized
    means Not authenticated!

403 Forbidden
    means Unauthorized

Single Signon doesn't mean log in once! It means only one system knows your credentials!
You need to configure other systems to adhere/subscribe to your single sign on system

How do you authenticate?  with user & password typically.
Sooo how do we transfer these single signon authenticated credentials to other systems?
Answer: tokens,SAML xml response
